{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_01HuWd6whvRQ5qmkf1z6Sm2c","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The app-client crash isn't a permissions issue — it's a queue-argument mismatch: `app-queue` in `/app` already exists with `x-queue-mode: lazy` (declared by `app-producer`, which includes that arg), but `app-client`'s own declare call omits it, so RabbitMQ rejects the redeclare as inequivalent. This is pre-existing environment drift, not something my permission fix caused. I'll resolve it with the RabbitMQ CLI (deleting the queue lets `app-client`'s built-in retry redeclare it with matching args) rather than touching any Deployment manifest."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3529,"cache_read_input_tokens":51772,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3529},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b0e57280-d153-406c-9b09-b030c5e3d4bc","uuid":"1cd2961a-8913-4f22-812a-f2218b9eb883","request_id":"req_011CcamhetdQY3uUaQoeduj4"}
