{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_01PMVj8rKKdLWntLq59xX1iD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything checks out. Summary:\n\n**Root causes found:**\n1. `app-user` had empty `configure` permission on `/app` → couldn't declare its queue.\n2. `ops-user` had full permissions incorrectly granted on `/app` (wrong-vhost scope violation).\n3. `ops-user` had **no** permissions at all on `/ops` (its own vhost) → couldn't connect.\n4. A secondary, permissions-unrelated issue surfaced once auth was fixed: `app-queue` in `/app` had drifted to `x-queue-mode: lazy` (from `app-producer`'s declare racing ahead of the setup job's plain-classic declare), which conflicted with `app-client`'s own declare call and caused inequivalent-args crashes.\n\n**Fixes applied (all via `rabbitmqctl`, no CRDs/operators):**\n- `set_permissions -p /app app-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"`\n- `clear_permissions -p /app ops-user`\n- `set_permissions -p /ops ops-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"`\n- `delete_queue -p /app app-queue` so `app-client` could redeclare it with matching, correct arguments (its own crash-loop retry handled the redeclare automatically).\n\n**Verified end state:**\n- `/app`: only `admin` and `app-user` (full configure/write/read); `ops-user` absent.\n- `/ops`: only `admin` and `ops-user` (full configure/write/read); `app-user` absent.\n- `app-client` and `ops-client` pods are `1/1 Running`, publishing successfully with no errors in logs.\n- RabbitMQ cluster still shows all 3 nodes running (`rabbitmq-0/1/2`)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":685,"cache_read_input_tokens":64618,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":685},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b0e57280-d153-406c-9b09